about me your life starting now mind body & fitness your life starting now mind body & fitness a stanford center on longevity discussion skip to content home about me about me my name is nikki yates and i ma senior at stanford university pursuing bachelor's degrees in psychology and drama major hobbies of mine include singing writing cooking and playing with my dog genevieve i became interested in the idea of total fitness after taking a longevity course with laura carstensen during my sophomore year of college following the completion of this course i found myself feeling concerned by the general lack of motivation to exercise and eat right among many americans the information exists and it's out there but why don t more people utilize it thus my goal is to find out how to motivate people especially elderly adults to keep their minds and bodies fit by talking to experts in the fields of gerontology nutrition physical fitness and others any questions comments or feedback is always appreciated thanks for reading contact me nyates stanford edu leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked name email website comment you may use these html tags and attributes a href title abbr title acronym title b blockquote cite cite code del datetime em i q cite strike strong search for recent posts how to get started lack of motivation interview extras wes alles wellness in the workplace you can do it too recent comments nyates on wellness in the workplace lily on wellness in the workplace cathy bonn on it's never too late to start archives december 2010 november 2010 categories blog posts interview extras meta log in entries rss comments rss wordpress org your life starting now mind body & fitness proudly powered by wordpress
